cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.BIO, cs.AI, cs.NEURAL

The paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques, specifically deep neural networks and convolutional neural networks, for protein secondary structure prediction. This falls under the intersection of computer science and biology, making cs.LG and cs.BIO the most likely categories. The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests cs.CV as a likely category. The paper also discusses the use of regularization techniques and sequence-to-sequence learning, which are common topics in cs.AI and cs.NEURAL.
